@Zenol : So I have downloaded the tensorflow-0.6.0-cp34-none-linux-x86_64.whl, renamed it into tensorflow-0.6.0-cp35-none-linux-x86_64.whl. The installation itself went successfully. But when i try the minimal example from the tutorial I get the "magical number" error.

Python 3.5.0 (default, Sep 20 2015, 11:28:25)
[GCC 5.2.0] on linux
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
import tensorflow as tf
Traceback (most recent call last):
File "", line 1, in
File "/usr/lib/python3.5/site-packages/tensorflow/init.py", line 23, in
from tensorflow.python import *
File "/usr/lib/python3.5/site-packages/tensorflow/python/init.py", line 50, in
from tensorflow.python.framework.framework_lib import *
File "/usr/lib/python3.5/site-packages/tensorflow/python/framework/framework_lib.py", line 62, in
from tensorflow.python.framework.ops import Graph
File "/usr/lib/python3.5/site-packages/tensorflow/python/framework/ops.py", line 24, in
import copy
ImportError: bad magic number in 'copy': b'\xd1\xf2\r\n'

Anything I did wrong?
